an outcome for only the most troubled couples, they see it as a last resort and this can mean that the divorce is often conducted in a way that makes the least amount of change for the man and his children. This can often mean that the ex-wifes rights are effectively erased and crucially any financial support arrangements that were put in place dissolved.

One young employee from a large manufacturer said he had an affair just 2 weeks after marriage, because he wanted to know what married life is like with someone else. In this instance the answer was a clearly unequivocal, it isn’t and he took measures to divorce his new wife and marry his new mistress.

With just over half of Japanese men eventually divorcing and an average marriage lasting only 8 years, it is little wonder that the wive’s dealing with the divorce process often find themselves fighting to hold on to what support is left to them and few men will compromise on their rights to child custody or home ownership.
